						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">SriK wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So, theoretically, I could do things like e.g. render large bosses on arbitrary backgrounds and just use the excuse of &quot;lol CHR ROM&quot;?<br /></div>CHR RAM and slow memory; it's more like a Sega CD (or PC Engine, or maybe even the PS1). Still has attribute clash. Still bandwidth limited. You can only really upload about 220 bytes per vsync without reducing the vertical height, or extended blanking gets you enough bandwidth to completely redraw the nametables at a visible height of ≈192 scanlines. Updating tiles is even worse; you could only upload the same amount of data as you consumed with a visible height of ≈40 scanlines.</div>

