						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Updating tiles is even worse; you could only upload the same amount of data as you consumed with a visible height of ≈40 scanlines.</div><br />A few mappers did combine CHR RAM with bank switching. Pinbot, RacerMate, and Videomation come to mind. So if your fictional cartridge has 128K PRG RAM, 32K CHR RAM bankable in 1K units, and a gigabyte of NAND flash, that could be close enough to unlimited CHR ROM.</div>

